This notification is in accordance with Section 1264(b) of the National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA) for Fiscal Year 2018. It informs about a change in the legal and policy frameworks related to the United States' use of military force and national security operations. President Trump submitted the last annual "Report on the Legal and Policy Frameworks Guiding the United States' Use of Military Force and Related National Security Operations" to congressional committees on October 16, 2020. On January 20, 2021, the President established new interim guidance for these matters, with further clarification on February 19, 2021. The purpose of this interim guidance is to ensure that the President has complete visibility on proposed significant actions in these areas while interagency reviews are conducted by the Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs.